                     A portrait of the 16th-century businessman Sigismund Baldinger by the German Renaissance artist Georg Pencz. The panel was restituted to descendants of the Hungarian collector, Baron Mor Lipot Herzog. It sold for 5.6 million pounds. Source: Christie's Images via Bloomberg  
                           

     
